  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia: Sustainable Pathways to Peace in Somalia - Countering Extremism with Social Healing and Community Based Reconciliation Ceremonies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To enhance community and civil society capacity, through the Quraca Nabadda (QN) process, as part of the process of reconciliation, trust, and reintegration of low-risk, ex Al-Shabaab (AS) combatants. 2) To enhance the Ministry of Justice capacity to support reconciliation.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Target districts&#x2019; local communities, with a special focus on low-risk disengaged combatants and victims; Federal Government of Somalia; Somali Ministry of Justice; and Somali Ministry of Interior and Federal Affairs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to reduce the level of violence and the threat of violence in the targeted areas and to enable the population to experience improved human security.</narrative>
  </description>
